---

## Race Priority Definitions

**A-Race:** Primary goal race. Peak fitness, full taper, maximum effort. All training builds toward this.

**B-Race:** Important race but not peak priority. Abbreviated taper (3–7 days), strong effort, used to gauge fitness.

**C-Race:** Lower priority. Minimal taper (2–3 days easy), used as hard workout or race-pace practice.

**Training Race:** Part of a long run or quality workout. Race effort but no taper.

---

## Notes for Coaches

Agents should reference this file when:
- Designing training plans (align phases with race dates)
- Prescribing taper protocols
- Planning race-specific workouts
- Providing race-week nutrition and fueling strategies
- Adjusting training load based on proximity to priority races

